frameDefinitions: A Protagonist has (or does not have) a Weapon.
The Agent is assigned to a Post where he or she performs a task associated with that Post.

Some Possessor, either a nation, institution, or private individual, controls a Force whose primary functions to defend the Possessor (or, in the case of an institution or individual, some area of land significant to them) and to carry out offensive actions for the Possessor.
A piece of Ammunition is a disposable artifact to be fired as a projectile in a weapon with the purpose of causing harm or damage.
An Agent or Cause makes a Patient sharper or duller.
frameExamples: Apparently, the suspect is <t>armed</t> with a shotgun.
The octagenarian inventor's vest repels armor-piercing <t><fex name='amm'>bullets</fex></t>.
John is in the basement <t>sharpening</t> his axe.
listRoleDefinitions: The destructive device that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has with them.
The time at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The location where a <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is assigned to a <fen>Post</fen> to perform a task involving a <fen>Salient_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Post</fen> is a location or station assigned to the <fen>Agent</fen> where a task or tasks are to be performed.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> is centrally involved in the task the <fen>Agent</fen> is assigned to perform. It is normally located at the <fen>Post</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> works at the <fen>Post</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> staffs the <fen>Post</fen>.
The <fen>Force</fen> is the body of soldiers that acts in military capacity for the <fen>Possessor</fen>. This role is incorporated in each word in this frame.
The <fen>Possessor</fen> is the nation, institution, or individual who possesses and/or controls the <fen>Force</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Ammunition</fen> that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to become more or less sharp.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that is sharpened.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of sharpness.  Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> sharpens <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> sharpens the <fen>Patient</fen>.
listRoleExamples: Sue was staffing <fex>the entrance</fex> when everything started to go wrong.
Working the front desk <fex>at a real estate office</fex> is not as fulfilling as it might seem.
The American invasion, which drew 26000 American troops against <fex>General Noriega's</fex> army, was the largest US military operation since Vietnam.
<fex>The smith</fex> sharpened many knives in the days before the war.
Several cuts into the log had dulled <fex>the blade</fex>.
<fex>The relentless impacts against the wood</fex> gradually blunted the edge of this axe.
